  <!-- This reflects XML into a database.
       GameDB doesn't allow duplicate elements. The formatting is
       strange for XML, but good for the database.
   -->
  <tree>
    <research>
      <!-- Arrival starts the plot. -->
      <Arrival points="10">
        We have long watched the aliens. Listened to the occasional strange digital chatter. A long frozen alien corpse sits in the deepest levels of a North facility. 
        But the situation is changing - the chatter is common now and deep space scanners are lighting up.
      </Arrival>
      
      <!-- Alien genetics / reason to be here plotline -->
      <Green points="20">
        The same kind of creature is in the vaults from 70 years ago. Compared to humans the Green is physically weak but mentally well developed. 
        Eyesight is more adapted to darkness than ours. Genetics are similar; we are studying the alien DNA.
        <required0 item="Green" />
      </Green>
      <Hornet points="40">
        The Hornet is a fast, mobile alien assault troop. Its exoskeleton is strangely well suited to the rigors of modern battle and may be capable of 
        briefly surviving vacuum. Genetically the Hornet is shows some similarity to the Green, but has unique DNA structures as well.
        <required0 research="Green" />
        <required1 item="Hrnet" />
      </Hornet>
      <Viper points="40">
        The Viper is a heavy alien assault troop with significant natural armor. The Viper is a genetic blend of the main alien DNA with creatures of 
        radically different genetics, possibly from yet another world.
        <required0 research="Green" />
        <required2 item="Viper" />
      </Viper>
      <Jackal points="60">
        The Jackal is a cyborg: robotics melded to an alien creature. The Jackal is a heavy weapons platform with integrated targeting systems. 
        The creature - whatever it is and wherever it is from - is genetically distinct from all the other aliens.
        <required0 research="Green" />
        <required2 item="Jackl" />
      </Jackal>
      <Prime points="80">
        The Prime is a greater variant of the Green, and statuary indicates a ruling class. Given the genetic splicing we see among the alien types, 
        we must conclude that the Prime are conquering and integrating races of the galaxy...and have now come to Earth.
        <required0 item="Prime" />
        <required1 research="Green" />
        <required2 research="Hornet" />
        <required3 research="Viper" />
      </Prime>

      <!-- UFOs and Alien Base Plotline -->
      <UFOs points="40" >
        We have detected 3 classes of UFOs. From smallest to largest we refer to them as the Scout, Frigate, and Battleship. 
        Note that the Battleship never actually lands; we will need to develop technology to infiltrate them.
        <required0 research="Arrival" />
      </UFOs>
      <!-- Note this is a good text length. Maybe one more line. -->
      <AlienCores points="40">
        We have retrieved an alien computer core. It is strange and adaptive, and much of its purpose is inscrutable. 
        But by connecting it to alien components and our own sensors, we are beginning to get new information on the alien agenda.
        <required0 item="Cor:S" />
      </AlienCores>
      <!-- longest text that fits. -->
      <Scout points="40">
        The Scout is a small ship undoubtedly responsible for many alien abductions and sightings in the past. Why they leave crop circles as a part of their 
        abduction/scanning missions is a mystery. They carry a small crew and easily fall to missile attack.
        <required0 research="AlienCores" />
      </Scout>
      <AlienTech points="40">
        Alien weapons show tech classes we've designated T1, T2, and T3. Perhaps weapon tech 
        reflects rank, status, or manufacturing capacity? 
        The cells used to power the weapons are unstable during transport. 
        We can take the guns, but not the clips.
        <required0 research="AlienCores" />
      </AlienTech>
      <Cell points="60">
        The power Cell is primary power source for alien weapons. We have researched techniques to field stabilize the alien cells so they 
        can be returned to the base. We can also re-charge the cells at the base.
        <required0 item="Cor:S" />
        <required1 research="Hornet" />
      </Cell>
      <Anti points="80">
        The anti matter cell is a short mega power burst for alien weapons. We can now apply the Cell techniques to field stabilize 
        the anti matter clips and transport them. We can also re-charge the anti matter cells at the base.
        <required0 item="Cor:F" />
        <required1 research="Viper" />
        <required2 research="Cell" />
      </Anti>
      <Frigate points="40">
        The Frigate is a medium ship that carries about 12 units, suited for both crop circle missions and city attack. 
        The frigate computer core is has much more sophisticated navigation and communication abilities than the Scout.
        <required0 research="AlienTech" />
        <required1 research="Scout" />
        <required2 item="Cor:F" />
      </Frigate>
      <BattleshipAttack points="80">
        The Frigate core can authenticate with the Battleships. This will allow us to dock with the hovering Battleship and attack them.  
        It is a very risky mission to attack a Battleship, but we now have the capacity.
        <required0 research="AlienTech" />
        <required1 research="Scout" />
        <required2 item="Cor:F" />
      </BattleshipAttack>
      <Battleship points="120">
        Well named, a fully capable alien vessel with massive firepower, including a main gun for city control or base destruction. 
        Intriguing however is that the navigation system is based on a homing technology. There must be a beacon, here on Earth!
        <required0 item="Cor:B" />
      </Battleship>
      <Beacon points="200">
        The beacon has been located. Without the ability to effectively navigate over deep space, the alien threat will be highly compromised. 
        This is our opportunity, but we feel confident that the beacon is very heavily guarded. Be prepared.
        <required0 research="Battleship" />
        <required1 research="Prime" />
      </Beacon>

      <!-- Items -->
      <ASLT-2 points="40">
        The versatile ASLT has been improved based on analysis of alien Ray Guns. ASLT-2 Gecko is a lighter, more accurate, and more powerful weapon than its predecessor.
        <required1 item="RAY-2" />  <!-- was PLS, but PLS is hard to get w/o destroyer. And destroyer hard to get without ALST-2 -->
      </ASLT-2>      
      <ASLT-3 points="60">
        The ASLT-3 Pulse Rifle is a hybrid of Terran and alien technology. It is a very
        effective all purpose weapon for wiping out the alien scourge.
        <required0 research="Hornet" />
        <required1 research="ASLT-2" />
        <required2 item="PLS-3" />
      </ASLT-3>

      <LR-2 points="40">
        The study of alien weapons has allowed to improve the range and punch of
        the Long Range rifle and upgrade to the LR-2 Marksman.
        <required0 item="RAY-1" />
      </LR-2>
      <LR-3 points="60">
        Based on alien stabilization technology, the Callahan LR-3 does high damage and
        is extremely accurate.
        <required0 research="Prime" />
        <required1 research="LR-2" />
        <required2 item="RAY-3" />
      </LR-3>

      <MCAN-2 points="40">
        Study of the alien Storm-1 has allowed us to improve the effectiveness of our 
        heavy weapon platform. We present the MCAN-2 Valiant.
        <required0 item="STRM-1" />
      </MCAN-2>
      <MCAN-3 points="60">
        Study of the alien Storm-3 and Jackal's targeting system has allowed us to 
        develop a devastating yet portable weapon platform called the MCAN-3 Dauntless.
        <required0 research="MCAN-2" />
        <required1 item="STRM-3" />
        <required2 research="Jackal" />
      </MCAN-3>

      <SG:K points="60">
        Shield Generators are based on alien field technology. They enhance
        armor. The SG:K protects against kinetic (mass driver) weapons.
        <required0 research="Cor:S" />
        <required1 research="Viper" />
      </SG:K>
      <SG:I points="80">
        Shield Generators are based on alien field technology. They enhance
        armor. The SG:I protects against incendiary weapons.
        <required0 research="SG:I" />
        <required1 research="Hornet" />
      </SG:I>
      <SG:E points="100">
        Shield Generators are based on alien field technology. They enhance
        armor. The SG:E protects against energy weapons.
        <required0 research="SG:I" />
        <required1 research="Prime" />
      </SG:E>

      <ARM-2 points="40">
        We have improved the strength of standard combat armor, with the
        same weight and mobility.
        <required0 research="LR-2" />
      </ARM-2>
      <ARM-3 points="80">
        Based on alien memory alloy technology, the ARM-3 is very good
        protection for field engagements.
        <required0 research="ARM-2" />
        <required1 research="Viper" />
      </ARM-3>
      
    </research>
  </tree>
  
